claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: Top portion of a journal article showing the Elsevier Vaccine journal header and the article title text (“Vaccine effectiveness of recombinant and standard dose influenza vaccines against influenza related hospitalization using a retrospective…”). The image only shows the journal header and article title, with no details on hemagglutinin (HA) microgram content per vaccine strain, and therefore does not support the claim. Note: Image only contains the title and header; no data tables or dosage information are visible.
